TY  - JOUR
T1  - True Interest Cost in Municipal Bond Bidding: An Integer Programming Approach
AU  - Nauss, Robert M.
Y1  - 1986/07/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.32.7.870
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.32.7.870
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 870
EP  - 877
VL  - 32
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Over $47 billion of tax exempt debt issues were sold to the public in 1982. A portion of this total was offered to municipal bond underwriters under a competitive bidding system using the criterion of minimum true interest cost (internal rate of return). The TIC bidding problem may be formulated as a nonlinear integer program. We develop a linearization which is embedded in a special purpose integer linear branch and bound algorithm. Computational results for several actual bidding problems are presented.
AB  - Over $47 billion of tax exempt debt issues were sold to the public in 1982. A portion of this total was offered to municipal bond underwriters under a competitive bidding system using the criterion of minimum true interest cost (internal rate of return). The TIC bidding problem may be formulated as a nonlinear integer program. We develop a linearization which is embedded in a special purpose integer linear branch and bound algorithm. Computational results for several actual bidding problems are presented.
